</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umahdi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mahdi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/18/02 4:20:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=204.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/solusek99/scimitar-c.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DAoC Now</span><hr size=1> I thought it was balanced to begin with. I think the need for balancing as some people call it, came from people complaining, nothing else. Its amazing how the gaming world of late is run by the most vocal minoriity, that really has no clue how to play. Its a shame gaming companies don't find a way to get better feedback, right now the feedback comes from the zergling horde instead of the people who understand the mechanics of how things work. <br><br>Anyway back on subject, Im enjoying the game still, mainly because of my friends. Thats what makes any game enjoyable, and the things are there to make DAOC a really good game as long as they continue to make postive steps by adding more content, more items, more rvr features and so forth.<br><br> <p><Strong>Mahdi / Truth De'andre</Strong><BR><EM>Truth 45+ Thane Palomides<BR>Mahdi 60 GraveLord Prexus</EM><BR><a href="http://www.jadedsouls.com"><img src="http://www.jadedsouls.com/art/sig2.jpg" width="268" height="60" border="1"></a><BR><EM>"Into the darkness I descend, but in the end into the light I will ascend."</EM></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uokilagincearbhall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Okilagin Cearbhall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/18/02 7:40:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=204.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DAoC Now</span><hr size=1> Been playing 4 months now and love it!  I've tried just about every race/class combo available and just can never decide which i like best.  kinda settled on the Armsman Class cuz I love melee and I like Camelot which is Albion Realm. Anyway.... DAoC is a great game for me, maybe not for all but i wouldn't trade my experiences for anything.  <br><br>Oki  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustinkybeef.showPublicProfile?language=EN>stinkybeef</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/19/02 6:37:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=204.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DAoC Now</span><hr size=1> RvR needs better tactics, and the end game has been getting bland. Seige equipment needs to work, im not talking about just rams and trebuchets. Keep taking and relic holding need to do something. Re specializing would help alot of people, especially with all the new spells put into once useless lines. The speed nerf was a hard hitter. Archers are slowly losing the edge they once had. Epic zones = death traps. Dragons are neat. I want more bridges and more water/river/lake features through out the frontier. Make a frontier where physical landscape plays a more vital role in RvR and tactics. Make spell crafting, and do it @#%$ fast. Make realm points do more than buy you potions that no one uses.<br><br>Shyde <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzukhov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zukhov</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/19/02 7:11:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=204.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.tripod.co.uk/EQZukhov/ZZport.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DAoC Now</span><hr size=1> Im still happy playing DaoC. I think they have gota pretty balanced game and listen to players well founded concerns. For example friars are now getting more spec points per level and better buffs.<br><br>More good stuff on the way soon (next 2 months)<br><br>- Housing<br>- Improved RvR with keep taking 'rewards'<br>- Spellcrafting<br><br>VN boards look exactly like whinplay forums used too but at least Mythic takes pretty quick action on decent customer suggestions and does not blindly follow some sort of weird 'vision' policy. <p><img src="http://www.nhbzone.com/up4it/up4it_images/zukhov.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaxximus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maxximus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/20/02 9:05:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=204.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DAoC Now</span><hr size=1> Still very enjoyable game for me.  Ive managed to get to level 43 and R2 L6 doing RvR.<br><br>Cloth casters die a bit too fast but thats due the fact we are the first target most times.  Our Circus RvR (mass of people with no plan at all) is in Emain in the Hib frontier.  Our best RvR is when we go off into Mids or in our own frontier it seems.  <br><br>Im not sorry I retired, but I am glad I didnt give away everything I had too (just in case +all that hard work in EQ) <p><div align="center"><img src="http://www.nhbzone.com/up4it/up4it_images/maxricco.jpg"</div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uarkanissoulhart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arkanis Soulhart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/20/02 9:38:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=204.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/1jmorales1/MO60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DAoC Now</span><hr size=1> I still enjoy it.  It is a very refreshing change from EQ.  Of course if your a hardcore EQ player coming to Camelot who's in bed with the PvE enviroment, you're not gonna like it as much.  <br><br>DAoC doesn't have the 'loot-first' way of life that is so ingrained in so may EQ players that it has created alot of conflict, both on forums and in game.  And as stated above, it's good to see the designers are constantly tweaking the game, adding content, adding quests, adding mobs.   <p><HTML><BODY><p align="center"><img src="http://members.home.net/1jmorales1/Soloris1.jpg" width="300"  height="55" /><BR>